"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"\\n# Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\\n\\n## **Common Deposit Issues**\\n\\n::::steps\\n#### **Funds not appearing in your dYdX account**\\n   - Verify transaction succeeded on source blockchain explorer\\n   - Check Noble explorer for IBC transfer confirmation\\n   - Ensure you've connected the correct wallet to dYdX interface; this is important for the autosweeping to happen from noble to dYdX chain and to sweep into your dYdX subaccount\\n   - Check [skip explorer](https://explorer.skip.build/) or [Range Tracker Tool](https://usdc.range.org/usdc) to see if relayers have picked up your transaction\\n   - Wait at least 30 minutes for all confirmations to complete\\n#### **Transaction stuck or pending**\\n   - For EVM chains, check if gas price was too low\\n   - Verify if transaction was rejected on source chain\\n   - For Skip bridges, check status on [skip explorer](https://explorer.skip.build/) or [Range](https://usdc.range.org/usdc) to see if relayers have picked up your transaction\\n   - Check if relayer networks are experiencing delays or outages\\n   - Verify all involved third-party services are operational\\n#### **Insufficient funds error**\\n   - Ensure you're accounting for network fees in addition to transfer amount\\n   - Verify minimum transfer requirements are met\\n   - For swaps, account for price impact and slippage\\n#### **Failed at swap stage**\\n   - Check if the DEX had sufficient liquidity for your swap\\n   - Verify slippage settings were appropriate for market conditions\\n   - Consider trying another deposit method that doesn't require a swap\\n\\n::::\\n\\n\\n## **Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting**\\n\\nFor detailed troubleshooting guides specific to each bridge, please refer to:\\n\\n### Bridge Troubleshooting guides\\n\\n::::steps\\n#### **Skip Transaction Troubleshooting**\\n   - [Skip Documentation Portal](https://docs.skip.build/go/general/transaction-support)\\n   - Input _tx_hash_ and source chain _chain_id_ into [Skip API](https://explorer.skip.build/)\\n#### **CCTP Troubleshooting Guide**\\n   - [skip explorer](https://explorer.skip.build/)\\n   - [Circle CCTP Status Page](https://status.circle.com)\\n   - [USDC Tracker Tool](https://usdc.range.org/usdc)\\n   - [dYdX Chain Explorer](https://www.mintscan.io/dydx)\\n   - [Noble Chain Explorer](https://www.mintscan.io/noble)\\n   - [dYdX CCTP Documentation](https://dydx.exchange/blog/cctp)\\n   - **Source Chain Explorer**: Etherscan, Arbiscan, etc.\\n#### **IBC Transfer Issues**\\n   - [Mintscan IBC Explorer](https://www.mintscan.io/ibc)\\n   - [IBC Relayer Status](https://ibc.range.org)\\n#### **Relayer issues**\\n   - Check status pages for relayer networks involved in your transaction\\n   - Wait for relayer networks to resume normal operation if experiencing downtime\\n   - Consider using an alternative deposit method if persistent issues occur\\n::::\\n\\n### Troubleshooting bridging issues\\nIf you encounter persistent bridging issues, follow these steps:\\n\\n::::steps\\n#### **Identify where your funds are currently located**\\n   - Use block explorers for each relevant chain (source, Noble, dYdX)\\n   - For Skip transactions, check the `transfer_asset_release` field in the [API response](https://docs.skip.build/go/api-reference/prod/transaction/get-v2txstatus)\\n#### **Try manual recovery methods if needed**\\n   - For IBC: Use Keplr or Leap wallet to manually complete pending transfers\\n   - For CCTP: Follow the manual process described in the CCTP section\\n   - For Skip: Contact Skip support through their Discord\\n#### **Contact appropriate support**\\n   - **Check the [dYdX Status Page](https://status.dydx.exchange)** for any known issues\\n   - **Join the [dYdX Discord](https://discord.gg/dydx)** for community support\\n   - **Open a support ticket** via the dYdX interface\\n   - **Skip issues:** [Skip Discord](https://discord.gg/skip-protocol)\\n   - **Noble issues:** [Noble Discord](https://discord.gg/noble)\\n::::\\n\\nRemember to include transaction details, wallet addresses, and a clear description of the issue for faster resolution.\\n\\n## **Best Practices**\\n\\n1. **Always start with a small test transaction** when using a new deposit or withdrawal method\\n2. **Keep your wallet connected** to dYdX frontend for auto-sweeping\\n3. **Save transaction hashes** for all operations\\n4. **Double-check all addresses** before confirming transactions\\n5. **Ensure your destination wallet supports** the asset you're withdrawing\\n6. **For large transfers, use Skip Go** instead of Skip Go Fast for better reliability\\n7. **Always move funds from sub account to main account** before initiating withdrawals\\n8. **Understand third-party dependencies** in your chosen transfer route:\\n   - Skip relies on their own solver network and DEX integrations\\n   - IBC transfers depend on the Cosmos relayer infrastructure\\n   - Coinbase deposits rely on Coinbase's infrastructure and Noble's IBC integration\\n9. **Monitor relayer and bridge status** during high network congestion periods\\n10. **Have backup withdrawal methods** in case one bridge or relayer network experiences issues\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#withdrawal-and-deposit-troubleshooting\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#withdrawal-and-deposit-troubleshooting\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#common-deposit-issues\",\"html\":\"\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#common-deposit-issues\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Common Deposit Issues\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#funds-not-appearing-in-your-dydx-account\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Verify transaction succeeded on source blockchain explorer</li>\\n<li>Check Noble explorer for IBC transfer confirmation</li>\\n<li>Ensure you&#x27;ve connected the correct wallet to dYdX interface; this is important for the autosweeping to happen from noble to dYdX chain and to sweep into your dYdX subaccount</li>\\n<li>Check <a href=\\\"https://explorer.skip.build/\\\">skip explorer</a> or <a href=\\\"https://usdc.range.org/usdc\\\">Range Tracker Tool</a> to see if relayers have picked up your transaction</li>\\n<li>Wait at least 30 minutes for all confirmations to complete</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#funds-not-appearing-in-your-dydx-account\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nVerify transaction succeeded on source blockchain explorer\\nCheck Noble explorer for IBC transfer confirmation\\nEnsure you&#x27;ve connected the correct wallet to dYdX interface; this is important for the autosweeping to happen from noble to dYdX chain and to sweep into your dYdX subaccount\\nCheck skip explorer or Range Tracker Tool to see if relayers have picked up your transaction\\nWait at least 30 minutes for all confirmations to complete\\n\",\"title\":\"Funds not appearing in your dYdX account\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Common Deposit Issues\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#transaction-stuck-or-pending\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>For EVM chains, check if gas price was too low</li>\\n<li>Verify if transaction was rejected on source chain</li>\\n<li>For Skip bridges, check status on <a href=\\\"https://explorer.skip.build/\\\">skip explorer</a> or <a href=\\\"https://usdc.range.org/usdc\\\">Range</a> to see if relayers have picked up your transaction</li>\\n<li>Check if relayer networks are experiencing delays or outages</li>\\n<li>Verify all involved third-party services are operational</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#transaction-stuck-or-pending\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nFor EVM chains, check if gas price was too low\\nVerify if transaction was rejected on source chain\\nFor Skip bridges, check status on skip explorer or Range to see if relayers have picked up your transaction\\nCheck if relayer networks are experiencing delays or outages\\nVerify all involved third-party services are operational\\n\",\"title\":\"Transaction stuck or pending\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Common Deposit Issues\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#insufficient-funds-error\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Ensure you&#x27;re accounting for network fees in addition to transfer amount</li>\\n<li>Verify minimum transfer requirements are met</li>\\n<li>For swaps, account for price impact and slippage</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#insufficient-funds-error\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nEnsure you&#x27;re accounting for network fees in addition to transfer amount\\nVerify minimum transfer requirements are met\\nFor swaps, account for price impact and slippage\\n\",\"title\":\"Insufficient funds error\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Common Deposit Issues\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#failed-at-swap-stage\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Check if the DEX had sufficient liquidity for your swap</li>\\n<li>Verify slippage settings were appropriate for market conditions</li>\\n<li>Consider trying another deposit method that doesn&#x27;t require a swap</li>\\n</ul></div></div>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#failed-at-swap-stage\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nCheck if the DEX had sufficient liquidity for your swap\\nVerify slippage settings were appropriate for market conditions\\nConsider trying another deposit method that doesn&#x27;t require a swap\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Failed at swap stage\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Common Deposit Issues\",null]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#bridge-specific-troubleshooting\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>For detailed troubleshooting guides specific to each bridge, please refer to:</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#bridge-specific-troubleshooting\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nFor detailed troubleshooting guides specific to each bridge, please refer to:\\n\",\"title\":\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#bridge-troubleshooting-guides\",\"html\":\"\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#bridge-troubleshooting-guides\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Bridge Troubleshooting guides\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#skip-transaction-troubleshooting\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://docs.skip.build/go/general/transaction-support\\\">Skip Documentation Portal</a></li>\\n<li>Input <em>tx_hash</em> and source chain <em>chain_id</em> into <a href=\\\"https://explorer.skip.build/\\\">Skip API</a></li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#skip-transaction-troubleshooting\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSkip Documentation Portal\\nInput tx_hash and source chain chain_id into Skip API\\n\",\"title\":\"Skip Transaction Troubleshooting\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge Troubleshooting guides\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#cctp-troubleshooting-guide\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://explorer.skip.build/\\\">skip explorer</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://status.circle.com\\\">Circle CCTP Status Page</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://usdc.range.org/usdc\\\">USDC Tracker Tool</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://www.mintscan.io/dydx\\\">dYdX Chain Explorer</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://www.mintscan.io/noble\\\">Noble Chain Explorer</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://dydx.exchange/blog/cctp\\\">dYdX CCTP Documentation</a></li>\\n<li><strong>Source Chain Explorer</strong>: Etherscan, Arbiscan, etc.</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#cctp-troubleshooting-guide\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nskip explorer\\nCircle CCTP Status Page\\nUSDC Tracker Tool\\ndYdX Chain Explorer\\nNoble Chain Explorer\\ndYdX CCTP Documentation\\nSource Chain Explorer: Etherscan, Arbiscan, etc.\\n\",\"title\":\"CCTP Troubleshooting Guide\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge Troubleshooting guides\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#ibc-transfer-issues\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://www.mintscan.io/ibc\\\">Mintscan IBC Explorer</a></li>\\n<li><a href=\\\"https://ibc.range.org\\\">IBC Relayer Status</a></li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#ibc-transfer-issues\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nMintscan IBC Explorer\\nIBC Relayer Status\\n\",\"title\":\"IBC Transfer Issues\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge Troubleshooting guides\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#relayer-issues\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Check status pages for relayer networks involved in your transaction</li>\\n<li>Wait for relayer networks to resume normal operation if experiencing downtime</li>\\n<li>Consider using an alternative deposit method if persistent issues occur</li>\\n</ul></div></div>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#relayer-issues\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nCheck status pages for relayer networks involved in your transaction\\nWait for relayer networks to resume normal operation if experiencing downtime\\nConsider using an alternative deposit method if persistent issues occur\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Relayer issues\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge Troubleshooting guides\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#troubleshooting-bridging-issues\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>If you encounter persistent bridging issues, follow these steps:</p>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#troubleshooting-bridging-issues\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nIf you encounter persistent bridging issues, follow these steps:\\n\",\"title\":\"Troubleshooting bridging issues\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#identify-where-your-funds-are-currently-located\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>Use block explorers for each relevant chain (source, Noble, dYdX)</li>\\n<li>For Skip transactions, check the <code>transfer_asset_release</code> field in the <a href=\\\"https://docs.skip.build/go/api-reference/prod/transaction/get-v2txstatus\\\">API response</a></li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#identify-where-your-funds-are-currently-located\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nUse block explorers for each relevant chain (source, Noble, dYdX)\\nFor Skip transactions, check the transfer_asset_release field in the API response\\n\",\"title\":\"Identify where your funds are currently located\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Troubleshooting bridging issues\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#try-manual-recovery-methods-if-needed\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li>For IBC: Use Keplr or Leap wallet to manually complete pending transfers</li>\\n<li>For CCTP: Follow the manual process described in the CCTP section</li>\\n<li>For Skip: Contact Skip support through their Discord</li>\\n</ul></div><div data-depth=\\\"4\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#try-manual-recovery-methods-if-needed\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nFor IBC: Use Keplr or Leap wallet to manually complete pending transfers\\nFor CCTP: Follow the manual process described in the CCTP section\\nFor Skip: Contact Skip support through their Discord\\n\",\"title\":\"Try manual recovery methods if needed\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Troubleshooting bridging issues\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#contact-appropriate-support\",\"html\":\"<ul>\\n<li><strong>Check the <a href=\\\"https://status.dydx.exchange\\\">dYdX Status Page</a></strong> for any known issues</li>\\n<li><strong>Join the <a href=\\\"https://discord.gg/dydx\\\">dYdX Discord</a></strong> for community support</li>\\n<li><strong>Open a support ticket</strong> via the dYdX interface</li>\\n<li><strong>Skip issues:</strong> <a href=\\\"https://discord.gg/skip-protocol\\\">Skip Discord</a></li>\\n<li><strong>Noble issues:</strong> <a href=\\\"https://discord.gg/noble\\\">Noble Discord</a></li>\\n</ul></div></div>\\n<p>Remember to include transaction details, wallet addresses, and a clear description of the issue for faster resolution.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#contact-appropriate-support\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nCheck the dYdX Status Page for any known issues\\nJoin the dYdX Discord for community support\\nOpen a support ticket via the dYdX interface\\nSkip issues: Skip Discord\\nNoble issues: Noble Discord\\n\\nRemember to include transaction details, wallet addresses, and a clear description of the issue for faster resolution.\\n\",\"title\":\"Contact appropriate support\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\",\"Bridge-Specific Troubleshooting\",\"Troubleshooting bridging issues\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting#best-practices\",\"html\":\"\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Always start with a small test transaction</strong> when using a new deposit or withdrawal method</li>\\n<li><strong>Keep your wallet connected</strong> to dYdX frontend for auto-sweeping</li>\\n<li><strong>Save transaction hashes</strong> for all operations</li>\\n<li><strong>Double-check all addresses</strong> before confirming transactions</li>\\n<li><strong>Ensure your destination wallet supports</strong> the asset you&#x27;re withdrawing</li>\\n<li><strong>For large transfers, use Skip Go</strong> instead of Skip Go Fast for better reliability</li>\\n<li><strong>Always move funds from sub account to main account</strong> before initiating withdrawals</li>\\n<li><strong>Understand third-party dependencies</strong> in your chosen transfer route:\\n<ul>\\n<li>Skip relies on their own solver network and DEX integrations</li>\\n<li>IBC transfers depend on the Cosmos relayer infrastructure</li>\\n<li>Coinbase deposits rely on Coinbase&#x27;s infrastructure and Noble&#x27;s IBC integration</li>\\n</ul>\\n</li>\\n<li><strong>Monitor relayer and bridge status</strong> during high network congestion periods</li>\\n<li><strong>Have backup withdrawal methods</strong> in case one bridge or relayer network experiences issues</li>\\n</ol>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/deposits-withdrawals/troubleshooting.mdx#best-practices\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nAlways start with a small test transaction when using a new deposit or withdrawal method\\nKeep your wallet connected to dYdX frontend for auto-sweeping\\nSave transaction hashes for all operations\\nDouble-check all addresses before confirming transactions\\nEnsure your destination wallet supports the asset you&#x27;re withdrawing\\nFor large transfers, use Skip Go instead of Skip Go Fast for better reliability\\nAlways move funds from sub account to main account before initiating withdrawals\\nUnderstand third-party dependencies in your chosen transfer route:\\n\\nSkip relies on their own solver network and DEX integrations\\nIBC transfers depend on the Cosmos relayer infrastructure\\nCoinbase deposits rely on Coinbase&#x27;s infrastructure and Noble&#x27;s IBC integration\\n\\n\\nMonitor relayer and bridge status during high network congestion periods\\nHave backup withdrawal methods in case one bridge or relayer network experiences issues\\n\",\"title\":\"Best Practices\",\"titles\":[\"Withdrawal and Deposit Troubleshooting\"]}]}}"
